coreInfo.label: none
coreInfo.description: Either the security controls have not been specified or cannot be controlled.

coreInfo.label: trusted
coreInfo.description: Trusted security zone, all traffic and access is by known and trusted parties.

coreInfo.label: dmz
coreInfo.description: Direct access to un-trusted network, no sensitive data. Controlled access to trusted zone.

coreInfo.label: un-trusted
coreInfo.description: Untrusted traffic, often public networks.

coreInfo.label: none
coreInfo.description: Unmanaged entity.

coreInfo.label: full
coreInfo.description: Fully managed.

coreInfo.label: limited
coreInfo.description: Partially managed.

coreInfo.label: no direct
coreInfo.description: No direct management.

coreInfo.label: active
coreInfo.description: High availability replica actively handling workload.

coreInfo.label: passive
coreInfo.description: High availability replica not handling active workload.

coreInfo.label: EVV WebApp
coreInfo.description: It is the server side application hosting the PWA.

coreInfo.label: EVV User
coreInfo.description: It is the main end user of this solution. It refers to the Clinician (or similar role) that visits patients at home or any other location in which is assumed to have poor or no connectivity at all. This user will interact with the application through a mobile web progressive application in an offline first approach.

coreInfo.label: EVV Supervisor
coreInfo.description: This actor is responsible for fixing Visits data before sending to the state (through CellTrak). All errors will be shown in the "Error Dashboard" inside CareLogic,

coreInfo.label: CareLogic Web
coreInfo.description: It is the main CareLogic application. It will expose a dashboard provided by Decisions so that EVV Supervisors can fix visits data. CareLogic Web will also be used to configure Service Documents and Appointments as usual.

coreInfo.label: CareLogic Mobile
coreInfo.description: As part of this solution we are using the Sync API and the Batch Component that interact with the CareLogic Mobile Application. Any changes that we make to these components could impact the CareLogic Mobile App and should be evaluated as such.

coreInfo.label: Sync API
coreInfo.description: It is the API that provides synchronization services, that is, the capability of moving data from the device to the servers and vice versa so that users can work offline. Data going from the device to the servers through this API will end up in a NoSql database used as "staging area".

coreInfo.label: QSI Batch
coreInfo.description: This component is in charge of moving data from the "staging area" (updated by Sync API)  to the corresponding tables in Oracle and Form.io.

coreInfo.label: CellTrak
coreInfo.description: It is a third party service that will collect all data from the visits and will format it and eventually send the data up to each state for verification. It serves as a faade between QSI systems and the states.

coreInfo.label: Integration EVV
coreInfo.description: It is an integration platform that provides messaging and middleware capabilities. It is the hub that will be used as an intermediary between QSI internal systems and external systems like CellTrak.

coreInfo.label: Form.IO
coreInfo.description: Third party product used as a forming solution. Capable of creating forms that will be embedded in the mobile PWA.

coreInfo.label: Mobile Devices
coreInfo.description: It is the physical mobile device in which the PWA will execute. Devices include iOS and Android running Safari and Chrome.

coreInfo.label: Decisions
coreInfo.description: Decisions will provide Rules Engines and BPM capabilities. Rules will be used to validate visits data and in case of errors, these will be shown in a dashboard exposed through CareLogic Web. If visits data is correct, it will be sent to CellTrak data aggregator.

coreInfo.label: API Mobile
coreInfo.description: It is a security gateway and the only entry point between client applications to consume backend services.

coreInfo.label: IAM Server
coreInfo.description: Server providing Oauth2 Capabilities. Used for authentication / authorization. We will use both, "Client Credentials" and "Authorization Code" workflows in this solution. At the writing of this document, we have Spring Security Server in place but a project to replace with PingIdentity is on-going. Part of this document will list future concerns that could impact this solution but that might not have an answer yet.

coreInfo.label: Form Builders
coreInfo.description: This actor is the main responsible for creating the forms in form.io and eventually expose them in the EVV WebApp

coreInfo.label: States
coreInfo.description: This actor represents each of the states (government) that will verify our visit data. We have no direct connection with them but are still an important part of the solution. Any changes or regulations they make can impact our system.

coreInfo.description: Stating Database to store data being moved from the device to the backend servers. It is also used to store audit traails.
